Eye extremely large and prominent (
Fig 53
): posterior margin exceeding posterior margin of mid ocellus in full-face view in most cases. Distance between lateral ocellus and eye shorter than 0.5 × of diameter of lateral ocellus (
Fig 23
). Palpal formula 3,3 (three maxillary and three labial). Notaulus absent on mesoscutum (
Fig 44
). Parapsidal line usually clearly impressed, sometimes weak and unclear. Anterior margin of petiole longer than its dorsal margin in lateral view (
