Hair on compound eyes short, 0.33 × to 0.5 × diameter of mid ocellus. Mesofemur in dorsal view, anterior face covered with dense subdecumbent hairs, but without longer hairs (
Fig 25
). Ventral margin of eye edged with darker pigment and minute punctures. Body bicolored, head brown and remainder yellow (
Fig 35
).
